VERDICT: APPROVED
The task is correctly implemented and should be accepted.

The diff delivers the required behavior for task #25: users can add foods while editing a meal, remove foods during edit (while preserving the backend’s minimum-one-item constraint), and submit the updated list through the existing meal update endpoint. Save-time validation now blocks blank food names and trims names before submission, preventing avoidable 422s from whitespace-only inputs. The backend change removes a duplicate challenge refresh call from `update_meal` while retaining a single refresh path, which is the correct conflict cleanup and does not regress meal updates.

Functional risk assessment: no blocking regressions observed in edited flow semantics; totals remain server-authoritative because update still posts item list and backend recomputes nutrient totals.

Security: none observed.

Next actions:
1) Mark task #25 complete.
2) (Optional hardening) Add/extend an automated UI/API regression test covering add-item + remove-item + save with trimmed names to lock this behavior in.

